<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 12 at 7:42PM EDT  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...ELEVATED FIRE WEATHER CONDITIONS THURSDAY...
Anomalously warm and dry conditions will continue on Thursday. High
temperatures will reach the upper 70s to mid-80s with relative
humidity values dropping to 25 to 35 percent. These conditions
combined with westerly wind gusts up to 25 mph will result in
elevated fire weather potential.</description>
